Hello,

There currently is no sugar facility to generate a matrix the way you 
want. The last option is probably the best thing to do for now.

Perhaps outer can help you :

NumericVector xx(x) ;
NumericVector yy(y);
NumericMatrix m = outer( xx, yy, std::plus<double>() ) ;
return m ;

Romain

